25|$|Azad {{was born}} in the village of Rarhikhal in Bikrampur, Munshiganj {{district}} on 28 April 1947. He earned BA degree in <b>Bengali</b> <b>language</b> and literature from University of Dhaka. He obtained his PhD in linguistics from the University of Edinburgh in 1976. He later served as a faculty member of the department of <b>Bengali</b> <b>language</b> and literature at the University of Dhaka. His early career produced works on Bengali linguistics, notably syntax. He is regarded as a leading linguist of the <b>Bengali</b> <b>language.</b>|$|R
