50|$|Dr. Byomkes Chakrabarti (also spelled Byomkesh Chakraborty or Byomkesh Chakrabarty) (1923-1981) was a Bengali {{research}} worker on ethnic languages. He {{was also a}} renowned educationist and a poet. His major contribution to linguistics was in finding out some basic relationship between Santali and the <b>Bengali</b> <b>language.</b> He showed how the <b>Bengali</b> <b>language</b> has unique characteristics, which are absent in other Indian languages, {{under the influence of}} Santali. His contribution was fundamental to research on the origin and development of the <b>Bengali</b> <b>language</b> and provided scopes of research in newer horizons in linguistics.|$|R
